6:
This is the Room of Idols. The 
Administrator is on the other side of 
that door.
9:
Heh. We've traveled all this way and 
the hostess won't even come out to 
greet us?
11: Stella, think you can open it?
21:
Don't push yourself. Your fever still 
hasn't gone down.
31:
That's right! Eat through the system! 
That's the taste of freedom, mon 
amies!
40: Pay... Pay for what you've done...
45:
You threw me away... You threw us 
away... Why... Why...
50:
Stella! Stop! Please! This hate... It can't 
be the answer!
59: You're right, Alk. This isn't the answer...
71:
She's back!
Dammit, Stella! You scared us!
76:
Wait. Is it just me, or has your fever 
gone down?
80:
I'm sorry, Stella. I'm sorry I made you 
go through this.
83:
But, you know, I've finally realized... 
My music CAN save people!
93:
Hahaha! How does it feel to be 
knocked off your pedestal? Look at 
you, rampaging like a wild animal!
99:
Ooh, is that desperation I detect in 
your voice?
Now you finally know the same fear, 
the same sense of helplessness you've 
instilled in us droids.
109:
Regis, that's enough. Go to a repair 
shop or something.
115: Diva! Oh, m-my DEar, sweet DIVA!
117: I saw her... I saw YOU, from the past!
119:
Don't you remember? You always used 
to say that music brought us closer to 
humans.
121:
Why... do you LOok at me... ssSO? C-c-
COME, Diva... Come inTO my 
emBRAce...
123:
That's why you taught us to sing. To 
remember old songs and make new 
ones.
Our melodies were supposed to be 
how we connected with each other... 
and with humans.
125:
So why would you keep us isolated? 
Why would you lock us in a cage and 
throw away the key?!
127:
Why... WhY?! I-I-I should bE asking 
WHY! WhY are YOU all TRYing to LEAve 
ME?!
128:
You are DROIDS! You were m-m-made 
to SERve huMANS! Why WOuld yOU 
aBANdon me like THis?!
139:
Stop wasting your breath. Words won't 
get to her!
143:
If words can't get to her... maybe 
music can.
145:
I don't care if my voice is fake. I don't 
care if it can be replicated a million 
times over!
147:
If there's even a CHANCE that my 
songs can make a difference... I'll sing!
